        "subject": "LU-4019 ofd: setattr don't udpate lvbo with object referenced",
        "message": "LU-4019 ofd: setattr don't udpate lvbo with object referenced\n\nwe shouldn't allow recursive lu_object_find() while object\ncan be destroyed. so release the reference to the object\nbefore calling to ldlm_res_lvbo_update() which lookups the\nobject on its own.\n\nLustre-commit: a4e8e2f71fb64e293cbf8db07f4608646fd7acd4\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/7795\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If34d89834e352b6d0b8129a6fb4377317833a78a\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Mike Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
